and the head.

36:29.729 --> 36:33.692
Your edges, they dig in with
every chop and slash.

36:33.692 --> 36:35.360
It will KEAL.
‐ Thanks, Doug.

36:35.360 --> 36:37.028
‐ Good job.

36:37.028 --> 36:39.072
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:39.072 --> 36:41.157
‐ Bladesmiths, welcome
to the strength test.

36:41.157 --> 36:42.701
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:42.701 --> 36:44.911
I will be throwing

36:44.911 --> 36:48.206
your Frankish throwing axes
into this large wall.

36:48.206 --> 36:50.041
Justin, you're up first.
Ready for this?

36:50.041 --> 36:51.710
‐ Yeah. I'd like to see it.

36:51.710 --> 36:58.633
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:19.362 --> 37:24.576
‐ Well, Justin, there is a ding
on this blade right here

37:24.576 --> 37:26.369
where my finger is.

37:26.369 --> 37:29.038
Your handles are comfortable.

37:29.038 --> 37:31.082
The problem I have
with them‐‐this bulb

37:31.082 --> 37:33.918
