a fighting axe as retention.

37:33.918 --> 37:35.754
A throwing axe you kind of want
to let it go.

37:35.754 --> 37:37.922
But, in all, your axes held up.

37:37.922 --> 37:39.758
Nice job.
‐ Thank you.

37:39.758 --> 37:41.342
‐ Nic, you're up.
You ready for this?

37:41.342 --> 37:42.802
‐ Let's do this.

37:42.802 --> 37:44.596
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:47.056 --> 37:48.641
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:48.641 --> 37:51.227
<i>I am super, super nervous.</i>

37:51.227 --> 37:54.022
I ground my geometry
relatively thin

37:54.022 --> 37:55.940
so I'm just hoping
they survive.

37:55.940 --> 38:02.822
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:20.632 --> 38:23.426
‐ Well, Nic, your edges
held up great.

38:23.426 --> 38:25.303
I can't even tell that
they've been thrown.

38:25.303 --> 38:28.264
The handles show no damage.
Nice job.

38:29.766 --> 38:31.893
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:31.893 --> 38:33.478
‐ All right, bladesmiths.

38:33.478 --> 38:35.688
This is our sharpness test
in the foot soldier attack.

38:35.688 --> 38:37.273
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:37.273 --> 38:39.984
This is all about
what the edges of your weapon

38:39.984 --> 38:43.738
will do on the protective
clothing of this foot soldier.

38:43.738 --> 38:45.490
Justin, you're up first.
You ready?

38:45.490 --> 38:46.950
‐ Yeah. Kill it.

38:46.950 --> 38:53.832
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:12.058 --> 39:14.143
‐ All right, Justin.
Your edges over here,

39:14.143 --> 39:16.354
as you can see
on the clothing on this,

39:16.354 --> 39:19.107
