the "Forged in Fire" champion.

40:10.033 --> 40:13.745
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:13.745 --> 40:15.580
Nic, congratulations.

40:15.580 --> 40:17.582
You are the "Forged in Fire"
Champion.

40:17.582 --> 40:21.085
Justin, unfortunately
your Frankish throwing axes

40:21.085 --> 40:22.879
did not make the cut.

40:22.879 --> 40:24.714
‐ Justin, both sets of axes
performed well

40:24.714 --> 40:26.382
in all of our tests.

40:26.382 --> 40:28.092
So this basically came down
to that small amount of damage

40:28.092 --> 40:30.219
you took in the strength test

40:30.219 --> 40:32.597
and the overall design
of your axes.

40:32.597 --> 40:34.057
‐ Yes, sir.

40:34.057 --> 40:35.975
‐ Justin, you did a great job,
but at this time

40:35.975 --> 40:38.227
I have to ask you to please
surrender your blades.

40:38.227 --> 40:40.605
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:40.605 --> 40:42.732
‐ I came here. I did good.

40:42.732 --> 40:44.275
I think I represented
myself well.

40:44.275 --> 40:45.777
And I think, if nothing else,

40:45.777 --> 40:47.111
these tests show that
I can make the working blade.

40:47.111 --> 40:49.781
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:49.781 --> 40:51.240
‐ Nic, congratulations.

40:51.240 --> 40:52.742
You're the "Forged in Fire"
Champion,

40:52.742 --> 40:55.787
and that's a title that comes
with a check for $10,000.

40:55.787 --> 41:00.249
Good job, man. Please present
your axes to the judges.

41:00.249 --> 41:02.585
